Tony Blair declared it would use the chance for a return as a British prime minister – adds however, that a comeback is improbable.
In an interview this evening on the occasion of the fifth anniversary of his elimination from the office the 59-year long one announced his opinions on different inside-political topics.
Since his resignation in June 2007 after a decade as a head of state Blair has avoided to a large extent to comment on British politics and restricted his comments in the Near East mostly onto the foreign policy and his role as an envoy of the quartet of the peacemakers.
Onto the question whether it would return gladly to the office of the prime minister Blair was summoned by the Evening Standard from London with the words: „Yes, secure, however, it is improbable that that happens therefore..."
